- just checked code: no block number/seedhash is required in the .info file so no need to take it as a param.

- this is all fine, but ultimately it should be a completely opaque interface - at present we have:

```
void ethash_prep_full(void *full, ethash_params const *params, void const *cache);
void ethash_compute_full(ethash_return_value *ret, void const *full, ethash_params const *params, const uint8_t header_hash[32], const uint64_t nonce);
```

these should become:

```
typedef void(*Callback)(unsigned);
void* ethash_new_full(ethash_params const* params, void const* cache, CallBack c);
void* ethash_compute_full(ethash_return_value *ret, void const *full, ethash_params const *params, const uint8_t header_hash[32], const uint64_t nonce);
void ethash_delete_full(void const* full);
```

`ethash_new_full` should handle caching opaquely and call the Callback 100 times passing 0..99 as the argument.

Before, it was up to the caller to allocate the memory required, passing it in as a `void*`. Now it should be allocated by `ethash_new_full` and deallocated by `ethash_delete_full`.

`ethash_compute_full` should act as it did before.

> minimization of the burden on recipe developers

The burden is not very significant. In my implementation, the compiler recipes simply contain a file `%RECIPE_DIR%\compiler.yaml.in` with placeholders:
```
{% set name='visual-studio' %}
{% set version='@PKG_VERSION@' %}
{% set feature='@PKG_FEATURE@' %}
{% set version_tag='.@PKG_FEATURE@' %}
{% set build_requirement='visual-studio-build @PKG_VERSION@' %}
{% set run_requirement='visual-studio @PKG_VERSION@' %}
```
that can be configured by a straightforward call to `sed` in `bld.bat`. (Recall that `%RECIPE_DIR%`, `%PKG_VERSION%`, and `%PREFIX%` are all pre-defined by conda-build. I assume that unxutils or MSYS are installed.)
```
set PKG_FEATURE=vc%PKG_VERSION:.0=%
cat "%RECIPE_DIR%\compiler.yaml.in" ^
   | sed -e "s/@PKG_VERSION@/%PKG_VERSION%/g" ^
         -e "s/@PKG_FEATURE@/%PKG_FEATURE%/g" ^
   > "%PREFIX%\conda-meta\features\compiler.yaml"
```

